---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const faq = [
  { q: 'Do you farm at night in Moonlight Peaks?', a: 'Yes. You play a vampire, so growing and nurturing is done by moonlight — just be back in your coffin before sunrise. Night farming is a signature twist on the cozy farming loop.' },
  { q: 'What is a Draculamb?', a: 'A Draculamb is one of the magical livestock you can raise on your farm. You can also keep an adorable three-eyed Hellkitten as a pet.' },
  { q: 'What kind of crops can you grow?', a: 'As a vampire you grow cursed, enchanted crops and glowing flowers — early examples include blood grapes, cruelcumbers, pumpkins, and nightshade. The full crop list, prices, seasons, and growth times will be added at launch.' },
];

const jsonLd = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Farming', item: new URL('/farming', SITE.url).href },
  ] },
];
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Farming — Moonlit Crops & Livestock"
  description="How farming works in Moonlight Peaks: enchanted crops and glowing flowers by moonlight, magical livestock like Draculambs, and magic that helps tend the land."
  path="/farming"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Farming' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Farm</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>farming</em> & enchanted crops</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        The farm is the heart of {GAME.title} — with a vampire twist. Here's how moonlit farming,
        enchanted crops, and magical livestock work. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Farming by moonlight</h2>
      <p>
        As a creature of the night, you do your growing and nurturing after dark — just remember to
        be back in your coffin before the sun comes up. It's the familiar plant-tend-harvest rhythm
        of a cozy farming sim, flipped to the night.
      </p>

      <h2>Enchanted crops & glowing flowers</h2>
      <p>
        Paranormal farming techniques lead to interesting results: you grow enchanted, glowing crops
        and flowers rather than ordinary produce. As a vampire your sustenance is cursed food, so
        you'll grow and curse crops — early ones spotted include <strong>blood grapes</strong>,
        "cruelcumbers", pumpkins, and nightshade. The full crop list with prices, seasons, and
        growth times will be documented here at launch.
      </p>

      <h2>Magical livestock & pets</h2>
      <p>
        Your farm isn't just plants. You can raise magical livestock such as <strong>Draculambs</strong>,
        and keep an adorable three-eyed <strong>Hellkitten</strong> as a pet around the homestead.
      </p>

      <h2>Magic & tools</h2>
      <p>
        Farming and witchcraft go hand in hand — you can water crops with telekinetic watering cans
        and learn <a href="/magic">spells</a> (including a watering minigame) that speed up farmwork
        and gathering. As you progress, you obtain new tools and develop your property to grow even more.
      </p>

      <h2>Coming at launch ({GAME.releaseLabel})</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Full <strong>crop database</strong>: buy/sell prices, seasons, growth times, where to buy seeds.</li>
        <li><strong>Best crops</strong> by season and profit.</li>
        <li><strong>Livestock care</strong> and what each animal produces.</li>
        <li>Farm spots marked on the <a href="/map">interactive map</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        {faq.map((f) => (
          <details>
            <summary>{f.q}</summary>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Pre-launch entry — crop and livestock data lands at launch. Related:
        <a href="/magic">magic</a>, <a href="/items">items</a>, <a href="/environment">environment</a>, <a href="/map">interactive map</a>, <a href="/beginner-guide">beginner guide</a>.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
